During National Truck Driver Appreciation Week, the United States recognizes the important role of truck drivers in ensuring the safe and efficient flow of goods across the country. With approximately 3.5 million hardworking truck drivers, they deliver billions of tons of freight each year, including essential goods like food, medicine, and clothing. Truck drivers play a crucial role in supporting the economy by transporting raw materials to factories and ensuring store shelves are stocked. They also contribute to disaster relief efforts by delivering life-saving supplies and assisting in the rebuilding of cities. The American trucking industry provides many Americans with a path to a good living and is a major contributor to the country's workforce and infrastructure. The government is committed to supporting truck drivers by investing in infrastructure and reducing unnecessary regulations.